column1: $ Siding Spring Southern Seyfert Spectroscopic Snapshot Survey (S7)

column2: S7 - Object name used in S7 products
Name in Veron and Veron-Cetty (V&VC) catalogue; alternative names.
V&VC - Right ascension in hours, minutes and seconds
V&VC - Declination in sexagesimal (degrees, arcmin, arcsec)
V&VC - Apparent magnitude band; 'V' -> V filter
S7 - Redshift.  Same as the NED redshift, but with small adjustments for ~7 galaxies
S7 - If special treatment for Sy1s (broad component subtraction) was applied (see paper)
S7 - Number of times object was observed with WiFeS
S7 - Date of the best WiFeS observation, which was used in Data Release 2
S7 - If conditions were photometric for the S7 observation included in Data Release 2
S7 - WCS quality.  N=Normal; S=DSS image was Saturated, limiting the cross-correlation accuracy; T=Telescope RA and Dec from cube header were used instead of cross-correlation results.
S7 - Total exposure time (s) for combined object frames of S7 WiFeS observation in Data Release 2
S7 - Seeing (arcseconds) for S7 WiFeS observation in Data Release 2, as recorded by observer from guiding measurements
S7 - WiFeS rotator position angle (degrees E of N, with respect to long axis of FOV) for S7 WiFeS observation
S7 - Mosaiced WiFeS pointings for this object?
S7 - The x-index (between 0 and 24 inclusive (for non-mosaics)) of the 'nuclear spaxel' in the S7 data cubes
S7 - The y-index (between 0 and 37 inclusive  (for non-mosaics)) of the 'nuclear spaxel' in the S7 data cubes
S7 - Estimated galaxy stellar mass (log10 M*/Msun)
S7 - Error on estimated stellar mass (log10 M*/Msun)
S7 - Error on estimated star formation rate (Msun/yr)
S7 - Optical diagnostic plot classification based on S7 nuclear spectra
Hyperleda - effective Radius in B band (arcsec)
